Since both terms were brought up, it might interest you, if you do't already know, that the full name of the instrument we call a "piano" is "pianoforte" and the name of its predecessor is the "fortepiano." Both names refer to the ability to play notes both LOUD and soft. Previous keyboard instruments had only one volume. So "pianoforte" really means "soft-loud". 

Why the name was reversed at some point is puzzling.

